#. type: Title ==
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:10
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "How is GBIF-mediated data used?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:16
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:13
msgid "Both data availability and data use have increased over time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:17
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:14
msgid "Data integration facilitates global research and access."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:18
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:15
msgid "Uses of GBIF-mediated data span disciplinary boundaries."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:19
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:16
msgid ""
"The scientific areas using GBIF-mediated data are conceptually diverse and "
"change in prevalence over time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:20
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Globally integrated datasets enable researchers to ask both basic and "
"applied questions at taxonomic, temporal and spatial scales that would be "
"otherwise impossible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:21
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:18
msgid ""
"The synergistic roles of observation- and specimen-based biodiversity data "
"highlight the value and need for deeper integration with phylogenetic, "
"environmental, phenotypic, ecological and genetic sources of data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:23
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Structural topic model results from 4,035 studies that used GBIF-mediated data published between 2003 and 2019."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:28
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:25
msgid ""
"GBIF-mediated data is also used for monitoring the state of biodiversity and "
"progress towards achieving the targets of the Convention on Biological "
"Diversity.  The increase in availability of GBIF occurrence data is one of "
"the indicators for tracking progress towards the achievement of Aichi "
"Biodiversity target 19 and GBIF is a key data source in the creation of a "
"number of other indicators, including the https://www.bipindicators.net/"
"indicators/species-status-information-index[Species Status Information "
"Index^], https://www.bipindicators.net/indicators/species-habitat-"
"index[Species Habitat Index^] and the https://www.bipindicators.net/"
"indicators/biodiversity-habitat-index[Biodiversity Habitat Index^]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:31
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:28
msgid ""
"While the utility of GBIF-mediated data is clear, the wide variety of "
"sources of data accessible through GBIF, spanning museum collections, "
"citizen science, metagenomics, among others, means that not all GBIF-"
"mediated data will be fit for every use.  Key components of using GBIF-"
"mediated data are understanding how to access the specific data that you "
"need from what is available in GBIF and understanding some of the common "
"data quality issues that affect the data so as to facilitate processing of "
"the data before analysis."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:40
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "*What is available to me?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:42
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:44
msgid ""
"Through the search functions on the website, users can access data that can "
"either be directly downloaded through GBIF or accessed from the original "
"sources following links that GBIF provides."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:44
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:46
msgid ""
"Remember that as a data user you should read and agree with the terms of the "
"GBIF https://www.gbif.org/terms/data-user[Data User Agreement^] that include "
"https://www.gbif.org/citation-guidelines[correctly citing^] the use of GBIF-"
"mediated data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:48
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:50
msgid "The data available to you are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:50
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:52
msgid ""
"Primary biodiversity data - occurrence, checklist and sampling event data "
"that is provided to users through the one of the 3 download formats:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:51
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Simple*: https://www.gbif.org/faq?question=csv-download[Tab delimited CSV^]. Only contains the data after GBIF interpretation. No multimedia included. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:52
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Darwin Core Archive*: The https://www.gbif.org/faq?question=dwc-download[Darwin Core Archive^] (DwC-A) contains both the original data as the publisher provided it and the GBIF interpretation. Links (but not files) to multimedia included.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:53
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Species list*: Tab delimited CSV with the distinct list of names in the search result and as a map visualization of the data.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:54
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "A range of metrics are provided for https://www.gbif.org/analytics/global[countries and regions^], data publishers, datasets and data searches that provide taxonomic breakdowns, trends in data collection and highlight data quality issues. For countries, these metrics can be also be downloaded in the form of a PDF activity report. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:55
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://www.gbif.org/resource/search?contentType=literature&literatureType=journal&relevance=GBIF_USED&peerReview=true[Searchable database of publications^] that have used GBIF-mediated data.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-use/modules/ROOT/pages/using-gbif-mediated-data.adoc:56
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:60
msgid ""
"Searches can be performed on the https://www.gbif.org/occurrence/search?"
"occurrence_status=present&q=[occurrences^], https://www.gbif.org/species/"
"search?q=[species^], https://www.gbif.org/dataset/search?q=[datasets^], "
"https://www.gbif.org/publisher/search?q=[publishers] and https://www.gbif."
"org/resource/search?q=[resources^], and each search function carries a set "
"of filters that allow for more refined searching and additional data "
"associated with the data, for example, https://www.gbif.org/occurrence/"
"gallery?occurrence_status=present[images^], can be found in tabs associated "
"with the search."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:1
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/description.adoc:14
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/solutions.adoc:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "Data access"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:6
msgid ""
"In this module, you will learn how GBIF's data is used and accessed.  You "
"will also learn about the handling of data quality and GBIF's data quality "
"flags."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:11
msgid ""
"The GBIF https://www.gbif.org/literature-tracking[literature tracking "
"system^] has identified over 5,000 uses of GBIF mediated data, most of which "
"are in peer-reviewed articles.  The majority of these uses are in the field "
"of ecology, but others relate to climate change, conservation, human health "
"and agriculture.  A systematic review of the use of https://www.gbif.org/"
"news/4tJNXqSLYd37InZxyPrU7E/data-integration-enables-global-biodiversity-"
"synthesis[GBIF-mediated data by Heberling et al. (2020)^] showed:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::fig3.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "Accessing GBIF-mediated data"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:32
msgid ""
"There are three points of access to GBIF-mediated data: http://www.gbif."
"org[GBIF.org^], the https://www.gbif.org/developer/summary[Application "
"Programming Interface (API) services^], and https://www.gbif.org/occurrence-"
"snapshots[cloud-based datasets^]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:34
msgid ""
"Using the website requires no programming experience and allows for quick "
"and easy search, filter and download functions for GBIF-mediated data, as "
"well as a range of additional tools and metrics that are not available "
"through API services."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:36
msgid ""
"API services allow continued access to GBIF-mediated data through other "
"systems and can be the basis for the development of tools that allow for the "
"interrogation of the data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:38
msgid ""
"Examples include https://www.gbif.org/tool/81747/rgbif[rgbif^], https://www."
"rdocumentation.org/packages/CoordinateCleaner/"
"versions/2.0-18[CoordinateCleaner^], and https://www.gbif.org/tool/"
"OlyoYyRbKCSCkMKIi4oIT/pygbif-gbif-python-client[pygbif^], as well as, "
"specialized tools that allow for more specific use cases, such as http://"
"geocat.kew.org/[GeoCat^] for Red List assessments."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:40
msgid ""
"With regards to cloud-based datasets, GBIF makes data available on the "
"https://planetarycomputer.microsoft.com/dataset/gbif[Microsoft Planetary "
"Computer (Azure)^], as an https://registry.opendata.aws/gbif/[Amazon AWS "
"Open Dataset^] and on a public https://console.cloud.google.com/storage/"
"browser/public-datasets-gbif[Google GCS bucket^] and https://console.cloud."
"google.com/marketplace/product/bigquery-public-data/gbif-"
"occurrences[BigQuery table^]. When using cloud-based snapshots, we always "
"recommend creating a https://www.gbif.org/citation-"
"guidelines#derivedDatasets[Derived Dataset citation^] for the records that "
"you use. When referring to the full dataset, please use the appropriate "
"citations as listed on the https://www.gbif.org/occurrence-snapshots[cloud-"
"based datasets^] page."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "intro-to-gbif::downloadoptions.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Cube*: An occurrence cube is a tab-separated csv file containing species occurrence measures (e.g. a count) summarized by taxonomic, temporal and/or spatial dimensions (e.g. a given year, a specific taxonomic rank, etc.).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:62
msgid ""
"https://techdocs.gbif.org/en/data-use/download-formats[Occurrence download "
"formats^] are fully documented in GBIF's technical documentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:63
#, no-wrap
msgid "Handling data quality "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:68
msgid ""
"Determining the precision and accuracy of the data for use is a key step in "
"determining the usefulness of the data for any intended purpose.  While GBIF "
"can support the identification of some quality issues that arise from within "
"the data publishing workflow, handling some quality issues requires "
"additional expert knowledge.  The two most common issues for which this may "
"be required are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Data gaps* - sampling across taxonomic groups and geographic regions is not equal and users may need to take into account sampling bias in their analyses before the data can be used effectively. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:71
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Taxonomic misidentification* - some taxonomic groups may require additional information to ensure that taxa have been correctly identified such as images, videos and audio recordings that accompany data or collector information.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "*GBIF Flags for Data Quality Issues*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:75
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-publishing.adoc:222
msgid ""
"https://techdocs.gbif.org/en/data-use/occurrence-issues-and-flags[Data "
"quality issues and flags^] are documented in GBIF's technical documentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:78
msgid ""
"During the indexation process, GBIF assigns issues and flags to data for "
"https://data-blog.gbif.org/post/issues-and-flags/[common data quality "
"issues^].  These most frequently occur from data entry errors or missing "
"data fields whose interpretation can be automated centrally by GBIF. These "
"interpretations are classified as:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Excluded* - where the original data couldn’t be interpreted, so is excluded in the interpreted fields.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Altered* - where the original data is modified in the interpretation process to be indexed in GBIF.org.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Inferred* - where an empty field is inferred using other record information.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:84
msgid ""
"Be aware that if you are filtering for data quality issues, you should "
"reverse the filter to exclude those data that have been flagged with that "
"issue. You can also see the verbatim data i.e. the non-interpreted data in a "
"Darwin Core Archive if you would like to validate the interpretation process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:86
#, no-wrap
msgid "*How can I improve data quality?*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:90
msgid ""
"Data publishers have the responsibility for improving the quality of the "
"data, and as a user, you play a key role in identifying where there are "
"errors.  If you should find an error in the data, you should contact the "
"publisher directly using the contact details that GBIF provides on the "
"publisher page.  GBIF also provides the ability for users to log data "
"quality issues using the \"Feedback and questions\" button on the menu bar "
"of http://www.gbif.org[GBIF.org^]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "Guides and documentation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:95
msgid ""
"GBIF supports its global community by offering comprehensive guides and "
"documentation, enabling the mobilization, sharing, and thoughtful "
"application of biodiversity information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access.adoc:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "Guides"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
